This paper is about compressing neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper deals with reducing the size of neural networks while preserving their performance. The paper also mentions using benchmark datasets, which suggests that it could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) if the datasets are image-related or involve tasks such as object recognition. Additionally, the paper uses a hashing function to group connection weights, which could be related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
